There are couple of ways to deal with this bi-directional relationship issue. I think `@JsonIdentityInfo` is the best way in your case.

What you need to do is change your `User` and `Product` class as follows.

```
//other annotations
@JsonIdentityInfo(
  generator = ObjectIdGenerators.PropertyGenerator.class, 
  property = &quot;userId&quot;)
public class User {
    // your code
}
```
```
//other annotations
@JsonIdentityInfo(
  generator = ObjectIdGenerators.PropertyGenerator.class, 
  property = &quot;productId&quot;)
public class Product {
    // your code
}
```
*Note: For more info [here](https://www.baeldung.com/jackson-bidirectional-relationships-and-infinite-recursion)*

Try the following:
```java
@ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.LAZY, cascade = CascadeType.ALL)
@JoinTable( name = &quot;user_product&quot;,
            joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = &quot;user_id&quot;),
            inverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = &quot;product_id&quot;))
@JsonManagedReference
private List&lt;Product&gt; listOfProductsForUser;
```

```java
@ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.LAZY, cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = &quot;listOfProductsForUser&quot;)

@JsonBackReference
private List&lt;User&gt; listOfUsersForProduct;
```

These two annotations ([@JsonManagedReference][1] and [@JsonBackReference][2]) avoid infinite recursion.


  [1]: https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-annotations/javadoc/2.6/com/fasterxml/jackson/annotation/JsonManagedReference.html
  [2]: https://fasterxml.github.io/jackson-annotations/javadoc/2.6/com/fasterxml/jackson/annotation/JsonBackReference.html


----------

I misunderstood the question. Both `listOfUsersForProduct` and `listOfProductsForUser`should be present in the JSON. The previous solution omits `listOfUsersForProduct`. To have both you need to use `@JsonIdentityInfo` as @ray already suggested:
```java
@JsonIdentityInfo(generator = ObjectIdGenerators.PropertyGenerator.class, property = &quot;userId&quot;)
public class User { }
```

```java
@JsonIdentityInfo(generator = ObjectIdGenerators.PropertyGenerator.class, property = &quot;productId&quot;)
public class Product { }
```

